snippet.textDisplay:
I think some folks (not me) are annoyed by this list because it wreaks of pretentious in a few areas. I like a lot of his list, but it is fucking bizarre to have a top 15 for one thing, presumably to stretch a list out, but then to place movies like Uncut Gems and Knives Out of all things above Dark Water or 1917. I mean on that note, 1917 should have easily made the list for it's Cinematography if Uncut Gems made it for it's (lack of) sound design. Having white noise and people yelling over each other is not an accomplishment, it's every holiday dinner ever :D


Still, a solid list with a few I have been meaning to watch. Thanks!

snippet.textDisplay: Ad Astra, Avengers: Endgame, and The Farewell were on my top 10 list. I meant to see Peanut Butter Falcon, Dark Waters, Ford vs. Ferrari, and Jojo Rabbit but sadly never got around to it. I didn’t want to see 1917, Parasite, The Lighthouse, Once Upon A Time in Wonderland, Uncut Gems, Doctor Sleep, The Irishman, Marriage Story, or Joker. I don’t like overly violent/depressing stuff. Although, I didn’t want to see Toy Story 4 either and I have mixed opinions on Rian Johnson so I still don’t know if I’ll see Knives Out or not. I can’t believe this was a 15 movie list. I’ve never heard of the other movies on your list. The Fanatic fake out made me laugh.
